On the day in question, I was rushing to the airport to pick up my family members who were arriving. In my haste, I made the ill-advised decision to drive aggressively and at a higher speed than permitted. I also allowed myself to be distracted by a text message from my cousin. These reckless choices led to the unfortunate outcome of crashing into a guardrail.

Fortunately, no one else was injured as a result of my actions. However, I understand the seriousness of the offense and the potential harm that could have been caused. My prior record, which includes 3 penalty points for speeding, reflects a lapse in judgment on my part.

Since the incident, I have had time to reflect on the inherent danger and potential consequences of such irresponsible behavior. I have come to realize the harm that I could have caused not only to myself but also to the innocent individuals sharing the road with me that day. This newfound awareness has compelled me to deeply regret my actions.

In terms of my personal circumstances, I am 37 years old with an otherwise clean record. I have always strived to be a law-abiding citizen and contribute positively to society. I am committed to learning from this mistake and ensuring that it will never be repeated. 

I humbly request your consideration of the mitigating factors present in my case, including my guilty plea and my genuine remorse for the harm caused. I fully accept the consequences of my actions and I am prepared to face any penalties deemed appropriate by this court.

In conclusion, Your Honor, I plead guilty to the offense of careless driving. I recognize the severity of my actions and the potential harm I could have caused. I stand before you today to acknowledge my wrongdoing and express my genuine remorse. Thank you for your time and attention.

Sincerely,

Charlotte Porter
